372
00:28:08,563 --> 00:28:11,623
Writers must not rely on their old works...

373
00:28:12,423 --> 00:28:14,363
and neglect producing new work.

374
00:28:14,563 --> 00:28:16,723
And I heard that he signed a contract...

375
00:28:16,963 --> 00:28:19,663
with your firm to write a new novel.

376
00:28:20,663 --> 00:28:23,763
Wouldn't it be better for him to focus on that?

377
00:28:25,463 --> 00:28:27,693
Well, I get why you're saying this,

378
00:28:28,563 --> 00:28:31,293
but we had high hopes for his "Fate".

379
00:28:33,393 --> 00:28:34,663
