What's the big deal?

536
00:38:18,025 --> 00:38:19,325
Then go away.

537
00:38:19,425 --> 00:38:21,525
As you know, I'm dependent on the typewriter.

538
00:38:21,625 --> 00:38:23,985
If I'm away from it for a long time, I lack energy and,

539
00:38:24,195 --> 00:38:25,925
I become way weaker.

540
00:38:25,925 --> 00:38:26,925
What?

541
00:38:30,025 --> 00:38:31,825
Then just go home.

542
00:38:32,625 --> 00:38:33,625
Just go.

543
00:38:34,385 --> 00:38:36,125
I really wanted to ask her...

544
00:38:36,725 --> 00:38:38,385
how much she remembers about me.

545
00:38:39,255 --> 00:38:40,255
Go.

546
00:38:40,555 --> 00:38:43,625
Stop making it complicated. Get lost.

547
00:38:47,385 --> 00:38:49,425
Did you say that to me?

548
00:38:49,555 --> 00:38:50,985
- No. - Dae Han.

549
00:38:51,285 --> 00:38:52,885
Don't be like that to your customer.

550
00:38:54,385 --> 00:38:57,285
Seol, I'm sorry to interrupt your dinner,

551
00:38:58,725 --> 00:39:00,785
but the light bulb in the women's bathroom burned out.

552
00:39:00,885 --> 00:39:02,195
Could you please change it?

553
00:39:03,985 --> 00:39:05,025
Fine.

554
00:39:07,225 --> 00:39:08,225
I'll do it.

555
00:39:11,195 --> 00:39:13,725
I said it's women's bathroom. Women.

556
00:39:27,085 --> 00:39:28,155
Mr. Yoo.

557
00:39:37,195 --> 00:39:39,325
Have you been well, Bang Jin?

558
00:39:40,255 --> 00:39:42,285
Goodness. How do you know my name?

559
00:39:44,325 --> 00:39:48,055
I heard it from Seol.

560
00:39:48,155 --> 00:39:49,985
It was nice meeting you.

561
00:39:50,225 --> 00:39:51,355
Wait.

562
00:39:52,485 --> 00:39:54,525
You are very strong.

563
00:39:54,525 --> 00:39:55,525
I'm sorry.

564
00:39:55,755 --> 00:40:00,455
I know it's rude, but you keep disappearing like a ghost.

565
00:40:01,585 --> 00:40:04,485
What is it that you want from me?

566
00:40:04,485 --> 00:40:05,525
Cell phone number.

567
00:40:06,355 --> 00:40:09,025
I recently came from the US, and I don't have a number yet.

568
00:40:09,025 --> 00:40:11,285
Then how about your address or another form of contact?

569
00:40:12,525 --> 00:40:14,825
I'm staying at my friend's for now.

570
00:40:15,055 --> 00:40:16,285
How about your name then?

571
00:40:16,625 --> 00:40:18,725
I want to know your full name.

572
00:40:19,225 --> 00:40:21,525
You could tell me your name, right?

573
00:40:21,925 --> 00:40:22,955
Right?

574
00:40:23,695 --> 00:40:25,325
It hurts. All right.

575
00:40:25,425 --> 00:40:28,125
I will tell you when you let go of my arm.

576
00:40:28,125 --> 00:40:29,425
My arm hurts.

577
00:40:29,785 --> 00:40:30,825
You mean it, right?

578
00:40:38,055 --> 00:40:39,655
My name is...

579
00:40:40,225 --> 00:40:41,885
Yoo Jin Oh.

580
00:40:42,385 --> 00:40:43,455
Yoo Jin Oh.

581
00:40:45,855 --> 00:40:48,485
Yoo Jin Oh.

582
00:40:49,855 --> 00:40:52,885
Your name is so amazing too.

583
00:40:55,385 --> 00:40:56,425
What happened?

584
00:40:56,485 --> 00:40:59,355
I just found out his name, and he disappeared.

585
00:41:00,155 --> 00:41:02,225
When will we become close?

586
00:41:03,555 --> 00:41:04,985
Jin Oh.

587
00:41:05,855 --> 00:41:07,455
Mr. Yoo Jin Oh?

588
00:41:08,885 --> 00:41:10,225
Mr. Yoo!

589
00:41:23,655 --> 00:41:24,655
My eyes hurt.

590
00:41:25,155 --> 00:41:26,955
Your eyes are piercing.

591
00:41:27,055 --> 00:41:28,855
If you're done with the staring contest,

592
00:41:29,625 --> 00:41:31,225
tell me what you want to say.

593
00:41:33,625 --> 00:41:35,955
- My senorita... - Senorita?

594
00:41:37,155 --> 00:41:39,525
That's the nickname I gave to Seol.

595
00:41:40,425 --> 00:41:41,925
Only I get to call her that.

596
00:41:44,055 --> 00:41:45,925
You are very cheesy.

597
00:41:46,755 --> 00:41:47,925
Go on.

598
00:41:49,125 --> 00:41:52,085
Why do I feel like you are ordering me around?

599
00:41:53,125 --> 00:41:54,125
Anyway,

600
00:41:54,585 --> 00:41:57,855
if you meet my senorita only to kill time...

601
00:41:57,855 --> 00:41:59,855
I don't have time to kill.

602
00:42:00,155 --> 00:42:01,655
Hence, I don't need someone to kill time with.

603
00:42:02,585 --> 00:42:04,625
Move onto the next question.

604
00:42:06,355 --> 00:42:09,225
How much do you know about my senorita?

605
00:42:09,225 --> 00:42:10,655
Do you know a lot about her?

606
00:42:10,655 --> 00:42:11,655
Of course, I do.

607
00:42:12,325 --> 00:42:14,925
Do you know how many years I've known her?

608
00:42:15,525 --> 00:42:16,885
How long have you known her?

609
00:42:16,885 --> 00:42:18,255
22 years.

610
00:42:18,355 --> 00:42:20,455
22 long years.

611
00:42:23,855 --> 00:42:25,485
I've known her for 80 years.

612
00:42:26,755 --> 00:42:28,195
Are you joking me?

613
00:42:28,385 --> 00:42:29,955
Are you immortal or something?

614
00:42:29,955 --> 00:42:30,955
Dae Han,

615
00:42:31,695 --> 00:42:33,355
I changed all the bulbs in the bathroom.

616
00:42:33,455 --> 00:42:34,455
I see.

617
00:42:34,455 --> 00:42:36,055
It looked as if someone intentionally broke them.

618
00:42:36,555 --> 00:42:37,625
It wasn't you, right?

619
00:42:39,255 --> 00:42:43,255
Of course, it wasn't. Why would I do such thing?

620
00:42:44,055 --> 00:42:45,755
You are funny, senorita.

621
00:42:46,755 --> 00:42:47,825
Sapsari.

622
00:42:49,585 --> 00:42:50,825
- Sapsari? - Sapsari?

623
00:42:51,655 --> 00:42:52,855
It's my nickname for her.

624
00:42:53,585 --> 00:42:54,885
Only I get to call her that.

625
00:42:58,755 --> 00:43:00,555
Let's go, Sapsari.

626
00:43:02,625 --> 00:43:03,925
Did you two fight?

627
00:43:03,955 --> 00:43:05,955
Are you in grade school?

628
00:43:07,355 --> 00:43:08,385
Sapsari.

629
00:43:09,255 --> 00:43:10,385
That's a nice one.

630
00:43:29,755 --> 00:43:31,685
Go in. I'll leave now.

631
00:43:33,355 --> 00:43:34,525
Okay, Brother.

632
00:43:35,525 --> 00:43:38,225
I knew you were going to be senseless.

633
00:43:52,155 --> 00:43:53,185
If you...

634
00:43:53,785 --> 00:43:54,955
remember something,

635
00:43:55,655 --> 00:43:58,355
tell me. Don't struggle alone.

636
00:44:06,785 --> 00:44:07,855
I'm leaving.

637
00:44:28,425 --> 00:44:31,985
Hooray to the successful fan!

638
00:44:34,525 --> 00:44:37,555
You said you'd come, why didn't you? Your dish was prepared.

639
00:44:37,955 --> 00:44:39,025
Aren't you hungry?

640
00:44:39,255 --> 00:44:41,525
I'm not hungry because I had mush.

641
00:44:42,585 --> 00:44:46,055
Looking for the man who disappeared like a ghost,

642
00:44:46,785 --> 00:44:48,855
I became mush myself.

643
00:44:50,655 --> 00:44:51,725
And...

644
00:44:51,955 --> 00:44:53,725
you were being all lovey-dovey in front of someone like me.

645
00:44:54,325 --> 00:44:57,225
You guys were so sweet. Do you like him that much?

646
00:44:58,155 --> 00:45:00,055
Yes. I like him.

647
00:45:00,155 --> 00:45:02,025
Goodness.

648
00:45:03,655 --> 00:45:06,625
How can you be so selfish?

649
00:45:07,155 --> 00:45:09,525
I have a lot of sins.

650
00:45:09,785 --> 00:45:11,255
I've got no excuses.

651
00:45:11,255 --> 00:45:13,955
And yet you came here. Why did you come?

652
00:45:14,355 --> 00:45:16,055
What did you come here for?

653
00:45:17,655 --> 00:45:21,085
I had to see Seol once.

654
00:45:21,755 --> 00:45:23,155
I had something to tell her.

655
00:45:23,155 --> 00:45:25,785
Why? Are you terminally ill?

656
00:45:27,685 --> 00:45:29,085
You selfish woman.

657
00:45:29,855 --> 00:45:31,685
You've been gone for 20 years.

658
00:45:32,325 --> 00:45:34,555
You abandoned your child and disappeared without a trace.

659
00:45:34,755 --> 00:45:36,425
Why did you appear all of a sudden?

660
00:45:37,755 --> 00:45:40,385
Never mind. Don't give me the reason. Don't.

661
00:45:40,585 --> 00:45:41,855
Get out of my house right now.

662
00:45:42,355 --> 00:45:43,655
Hurry before Seol comes.

663
00:45:46,155 --> 00:45:47,325
We're home.

664
00:45:54,355 --> 00:45:55,355
Who is she?

665
00:46:13,385 --> 00:46:14,585
Mom?

666
00:46:21,955 --> 00:46:22,985
Seol.

667
00:46:29,055 --> 00:46:30,055
Mom.

668
00:46:31,255 --> 00:46:32,285
Is that you?

669
00:46:53,125 --> 00:46:54,185
I want to...

670
00:46:55,855 --> 00:46:57,055
apologize.

671
00:47:01,125 --> 00:47:02,825
I won't ask you to forgive me.

672
00:47:06,055 --> 00:47:07,155
How...

673
00:47:09,255 --> 00:47:10,685
have you been?

674
00:47:14,955 --> 00:47:18,785
How could I have wished for happiness after abandoning my child?

675
00:47:20,855 --> 00:47:22,585
I just lived somehow.

676
00:47:22,885 --> 00:47:24,525
Then you should've just...

677
00:47:25,355 --> 00:47:26,955
continued living like that.

678
00:47:28,055 --> 00:47:29,425
Why did you come find me?

679
00:47:30,525 --> 00:47:31,955
- Seol. - Why?

680
00:47:33,325 --> 00:47:34,555
Did you run out of money?

681
00:47:36,555 --> 00:47:37,825
You abandoned your child...

682
00:47:38,885 --> 00:47:42,685
and left to be with a man to be happy.

683
00:47:43,855 --> 00:47:46,925
This is too shabby. It's all too disappointing for me.

684
00:47:53,555 --> 00:47:55,085
On the day Dad died,

685
00:47:57,625 --> 00:47:59,225
I thought you'd come to his funeral.

686
00:48:00,785 --> 00:48:02,525
Even if you were divorced,

687
00:48:03,625 --> 00:48:05,155
and even if you abandoned your child.

688
00:48:06,355 --> 00:48:08,125
I thought you'd come and ask me to live with you...

689
00:48:09,055 --> 00:48:10,485
when you see me being all alone.

690
00:48:11,655 --> 00:48:12,825
I thought I'd reject...

691
00:48:13,455 --> 00:48:15,825
just once, only once...

692
00:48:16,485 --> 00:48:17,725
and then follow you.

693
00:48:19,555 --> 00:48:21,085
I waited for you with that thought.

694
00:48:22,925 --> 00:48:24,025
I am sorry.

695
00:48:27,585 --> 00:48:29,355
I am so sorry, darling.

696
00:48:32,485 --> 00:48:34,755
I shouldn't have abandoned you like that.

697
00:48:40,625 --> 00:48:41,785
Please leave now.

698
00:48:42,455 --> 00:48:44,085
I don't want to see you anymore.

699
00:48:44,655 --> 00:48:47,355
My wound just got healed, and you just threw salt at it.

700
00:48:48,225 --> 00:48:49,225
Do you...

701
00:48:51,055 --> 00:48:52,355
still see your past life?

702
00:48:54,955 --> 00:48:56,325
You told me that when you were little.

703
00:48:57,025 --> 00:48:58,655
You said you killed someone with a gun.

704
00:48:58,955 --> 00:49:00,855
You said it made you hurt and sad.

705
00:49:02,285 --> 00:49:03,455
Did you...

706
00:49:04,025 --> 00:49:05,025
remember...

707
00:49:05,685 --> 00:49:08,125
anything else?

708
00:49:09,885 --> 00:49:11,485
Did you come here to ask me that?

709
00:49:12,325 --> 00:49:14,355
Why? Will you come back to me...

710
00:49:14,355 --> 00:49:16,725
if I say I am totally normal now?

711
00:49:17,785 --> 00:49:18,855
No.

712
00:49:24,885 --> 00:49:25,985
I've come...

713
00:49:27,255 --> 00:49:29,785
to tell you the real reason for leaving you.

714
00:49:31,485 --> 00:49:34,555
What other reason was there other than the man?

715
00:49:39,725 --> 00:49:40,785
I also...

716
00:49:42,785 --> 00:49:44,485
have memories of my past life.

717
00:49:53,228 --> 00:49:57,028
So you knew about my past life...

718
00:49:58,398 --> 00:50:00,228
that I remember?

719
00:50:02,258 --> 00:50:04,028
You'll find it hard to believe, but that's right.

720
00:50:05,528 --> 00:50:07,028
And you and I were...

721
00:50:07,898 --> 00:50:10,798
in the same space at the same time?

722
00:50:16,098 --> 00:50:19,858
But how can that be the reason you left me?

723
00:50:21,658 --> 00:50:22,698
I was scared...

724
00:50:24,298 --> 00:50:28,098
that our ill-fated relationship from our past lives might be repeated...

725
00:50:29,328 --> 00:50:33,098
and that you might remember things that you shouldn't remember.

726
00:50:33,298 --> 00:50:34,798
I was terrified.

727
00:50:36,498 --> 00:50:39,128
What are the things that I shouldn't remember?

728
00:50:41,198 --> 00:50:43,098
Memories of what?

729
00:50:48,498 --> 00:50:51,928
I came to see you because there's something I have to tell you.

730
00:51:04,028 --> 00:51:05,458
Stay away from that man.

731
00:51:07,898 --> 00:51:09,028
Don't meet him.

732
00:51:09,428 --> 00:51:12,198
You guys must not cross paths.

733
00:51:13,928 --> 00:51:15,258
What are you talking about?

734
00:51:16,328 --> 00:51:18,998
Don't be so cryptic and vague.

735
00:51:19,498 --> 00:51:21,798
- Tell me everything you know. - I can't.

736
00:51:22,728 --> 00:51:26,328
It might unleash the memories I tried so hard to lock up.

737
00:51:26,658 --> 00:51:28,358
- Mom. - Just remember this, Seol.

738
00:51:29,158 --> 00:51:32,798
You must not let any of the ill-fated relationships repeat.

739
00:51:33,028 --> 00:51:34,358
Don't even think about your past life.

740
00:51:34,798 --> 00:51:37,798
Forget everything and just live your life now. That's all you have to do.

741
00:51:38,358 --> 00:51:39,498
You must.

742
00:51:48,328 --> 00:51:51,498
I wanted Seol to be the first person to see me when I reveal myself.

743
00:51:51,828 --> 00:51:54,958
How did I get caught by Bang Jin like that?

744
00:51:55,798 --> 00:51:57,598
That was so stressful.

745
00:51:58,028 --> 00:51:59,098
Aren't you going to work?

746
00:52:02,098 --> 00:52:04,458
My gosh, I see that you've perked up.

747
00:52:04,798 --> 00:52:07,498
I am fully recharged.

748
00:52:08,328 --> 00:52:12,698
By the way, do ghosts lose their abilities when they're tired?

749
00:52:13,028 --> 00:52:15,798
I'm different from normal ghosts. Because I dwell in the typewriter,

750
00:52:15,858 --> 00:52:18,958
my abilities become limited when I'm far away from the typewriter.

751
00:52:19,058 --> 00:52:20,058
What?

752
00:52:21,028 --> 00:52:23,158
Then you're not any better than us humans.

753
00:52:23,758 --> 00:52:26,198
Ghosts don't have it better than humans to begin with.

754
00:52:26,858 --> 00:52:29,428
I can't reveal myself in front of the person I like,

755
00:52:29,428 --> 00:52:31,458
and I can't even look at her in the eye and talk to her.

756
00:52:31,858 --> 00:52:33,428
I can't grow old with her either.

757
00:52:35,098 --> 00:52:37,158
People who live only because they can't die...

758
00:52:37,898 --> 00:52:39,798
might actually envy ghosts.

759
00:52:40,028 --> 00:52:42,628
If you're that jealous, how about we swap?

760
00:52:42,958 --> 00:52:44,028
Do you want to die?

761
00:52:44,358 --> 00:52:45,858
I'm already dead.

762
00:52:48,728 --> 00:52:52,698
Anyway, I have hope now that Seol has remembered me.

763
00:52:53,828 --> 00:52:56,328
I should find a way to reveal myself to her as soon as possible.

764
00:52:56,858 --> 00:52:58,658
Then shall we begin?

765
00:53:04,058 --> 00:53:08,028
Unpleasant things happen whenever I hear that sound.

766
00:53:14,658 --> 00:53:17,898
Ominous premonitions are never wrong.

767
00:53:19,158 --> 00:53:21,458
Hey, Se Ju.

768
00:53:21,928 --> 00:53:23,058
How have you been?

769
00:53:25,398 --> 00:53:27,628
Do you even compete with alcohol now?

770
00:53:27,858 --> 00:53:28,928
You punk.

771
00:53:32,058 --> 00:53:33,258
It's good to see you.

772
00:53:34,498 --> 00:53:35,958
How many years has it been?

773
00:53:36,798 --> 00:53:39,828
Behave yourself if you're going to get drunk. Don't be ridiculous.

774
00:53:41,498 --> 00:53:44,558
This isn't your place. I'll call a driver for you, so just go home.

775
00:53:53,928 --> 00:53:56,428
Se Ju, can you please...

776
00:53:59,528 --> 00:54:01,358
help me out this once?

777
00:54:04,558 --> 00:54:05,758
What are you doing right now?

778
00:54:06,298 --> 00:54:08,628
Do you want to feel mortified later? Get up.

779
00:54:08,898 --> 00:54:10,958
Unless you want to regret yourself to death tomorrow morning.

780
00:54:10,958 --> 00:54:12,198
The first draft of "Fate".

781
00:54:16,098 --> 00:54:17,628
Can you give it to me?

782
00:54:22,058 --> 00:54:23,698
Is that why you're here?

783
00:54:23,898 --> 00:54:25,658
My mighty and just father...

784
00:54:27,158 --> 00:54:28,458
wants me to disclose everything...

785
00:54:29,598 --> 00:54:32,958
and start afresh from the bottom.

786
00:54:34,998 --> 00:54:36,058
But you know.

787
00:54:36,498 --> 00:54:37,958
I can't do that.

788
00:54:38,158 --> 00:54:40,498
I can't rise up like this again with my abilities alone.

789
00:54:40,558 --> 00:54:43,058
- Tae Min. - I'd rather die.

790
00:54:44,458 --> 00:54:46,928
If people look at me with eyes full of contempt...

791
00:54:51,258 --> 00:54:52,528
I can't tolerate it.

792
00:54:54,558 --> 00:54:55,628
I won't be able to take it.

793
00:55:07,428 --> 00:55:08,928
All right. I'll give it to you.

794
00:55:09,398 --> 00:55:11,258
You can have it, so just get up already...

795
00:55:48,758 --> 00:55:52,058
Don't tell me that you're feeling compassion towards him.

796
00:55:53,498 --> 00:55:56,098
He and I used to be roommates.

797
00:55:56,698 --> 00:55:58,158
I can do this much for him.

798
00:55:58,498 --> 00:56:00,328
Don't trust that guy.

799
00:56:01,058 --> 00:56:03,598
He was two-faced even in the old days.

800
00:56:03,998 --> 00:56:05,028
The old days?

801
00:56:06,398 --> 00:56:08,328
- Does that mean... - That's right.

802
00:56:09,128 --> 00:56:10,928
He was in Kyungsung too.

803
00:56:12,028 --> 00:56:13,398
Why didn't you tell me sooner?

804
00:56:13,858 --> 00:56:15,458
I wanted to observe him first.

805
00:56:16,058 --> 00:56:19,358
Villains aren't always reincarnated as villains.

806
00:56:19,698 --> 00:56:22,898
Then did you sign the contract with me...

807
00:56:23,598 --> 00:56:26,358
in order to pull him away from Seol?

808
00:56:27,328 --> 00:56:28,628
That is one of the reasons.

809
00:56:29,258 --> 00:56:32,898
I wanted to track down two people in order to find out how I died,

810
00:56:34,998 --> 00:56:37,298
and he's one of them.

811
00:56:37,898 --> 00:56:39,228
Who's the other one?

812
00:56:41,028 --> 00:56:44,758
The madam at Carpe Diem, Sophia.

813
00:57:20,898 --> 00:57:23,358
Had I known my heart would be tattered into pieces like this,

814
00:57:24,328 --> 00:57:26,228
I would've just stayed by your side.

815
00:57:29,398 --> 00:57:30,458
I'm sorry.

816
00:57:33,098 --> 00:57:34,398
I'm sorry, Seol.

817
00:57:54,758 --> 00:57:55,958
Just a second.

818
00:58:00,898 --> 00:58:02,458
You better turn around.

819
00:58:03,728 --> 00:58:04,798
Otherwise, I'll never see you again.

820
00:58:06,398 --> 00:58:08,928
I'll never look for you. I really mean it.

821
00:58:21,398 --> 00:58:22,428
I'm sorry,

822
00:58:24,098 --> 00:58:25,828
but I don't believe in what you said.

823
00:58:27,358 --> 00:58:28,528
I won't be like you.

824
00:58:30,598 --> 00:58:33,828
I won't leave those I love just because of my past life.

825
00:58:35,098 --> 00:58:37,798
I'm not scared at all. I'm not afraid at all.

826
00:58:40,158 --> 00:58:41,228
Because...

827
00:58:42,928 --> 00:58:45,228
I'm not alone. I'm going to overcome it together.

828
00:58:48,758 --> 00:58:51,428
- Seol. - What I can't forgive...

829
00:58:52,698 --> 00:58:55,758
is that you didn't even think of overcoming it together with me.

830
00:58:55,958 --> 00:58:56,958
Even now,

831
00:58:57,358 --> 00:58:58,828
you're running away.

832
00:59:04,828 --> 00:59:05,828
The fate...

833
00:59:07,598 --> 00:59:10,628
The ill fate might be repeated.

834
00:59:10,898 --> 00:59:11,998
No, it won't.

835
00:59:12,858 --> 00:59:14,358
Fate can be changed.

836
00:59:14,558 --> 00:59:15,798
And I'm not like you.

837
00:59:16,258 --> 00:59:18,998
I would never live like you.

838
00:59:36,228 --> 00:59:39,628
What have two people done to us?

839
00:59:39,628 --> 00:59:41,728
I can't remember in detail,

840
00:59:42,158 --> 00:59:43,528
but I clearly remember...

841
00:59:43,528 --> 00:59:47,028
the name and the face of the two, although my memory was erased.

842
00:59:48,158 --> 00:59:50,398
I'm sure they're related to...

843
00:59:51,528 --> 00:59:52,558
my death.

844
01:00:13,658 --> 01:00:15,358
Hey, Sapsari.

845
01:00:16,528 --> 01:00:17,798
You called me at the right moment.

846
01:00:18,698 --> 01:00:20,658
I wanted to take some rest.

847
01:00:21,358 --> 01:00:23,058
You told me I should tell you when I have problems.

848
01:00:24,158 --> 01:00:26,058
Now is the moment.

849
01:00:26,598 --> 01:00:27,898
Can I see you for a moment?

850
01:00:28,098 --> 01:00:29,158
Where are you now?

851
01:00:45,728 --> 01:00:47,328
All right. I'll be there soon.

852
01:00:47,828 --> 01:00:51,658
I might arrive later than you, so wait inside.

853
01:01:50,058 --> 01:01:51,658
("Fate", First draft)

854
01:01:53,598 --> 01:01:55,498
("Fate", First draft)

855
01:02:05,058 --> 01:02:08,128
You're still living like a rat.

856
01:02:08,458 --> 01:02:09,458
Heo Young Min.

857
01:02:27,798 --> 01:02:28,798
Who are you?

858
01:02:32,928 --> 01:02:34,758
He can see me?

859
01:02:45,598 --> 01:02:46,798
Don't meet him.

860
01:02:47,128 --> 01:02:49,858
You guys must not cross paths.

861
01:02:52,428 --> 01:02:54,028
Us meeting each other...

862
01:02:54,028 --> 01:02:55,758
was not a coincidence.

863
01:02:55,758 --> 01:02:57,958
There must be a reason.

864
01:02:58,658 --> 01:03:00,998
The fate... The ill fate might be...

865
01:03:01,558 --> 01:03:03,228
repeated.

866
01:03:04,798 --> 01:03:07,258
Shoot. It's an order.

867
01:03:14,858 --> 01:03:15,858
Typewriter?

868
01:03:16,328 --> 01:03:18,998
You know, the typewriter in my workroom.

869
01:03:19,498 --> 01:03:21,428
It's what I used to use in my past life.

870
01:03:22,428 --> 01:03:24,498
The pocket watch you have...

871
01:03:25,058 --> 01:03:27,228
also used to be mine in my past life.

872
01:04:05,198 --> 01:04:06,198
Seol.

873
01:04:09,728 --> 01:04:10,758
What's wrong?

874
01:04:11,458 --> 01:04:12,558
What happened?

875
01:04:13,858 --> 01:04:14,898
Are you sick?

876
01:04:17,858 --> 01:04:19,128
Just remember this, Seol.

877
01:04:19,828 --> 01:04:23,458
You must not let any of the ill-fated relationships repeat.

878
01:05:06,058 --> 01:05:08,728
(Chicago Typewriter)

879
01:05:08,828 --> 01:05:11,528
How will the novel end?

880
01:05:11,528 --> 01:05:13,098
Do you not want it to be finished?

881
01:05:13,098 --> 01:05:15,398
I just think I'll be sad...

882
01:05:15,398 --> 01:05:16,698
if its ending is tragic.

883
01:05:16,698 --> 01:05:19,528
You're really handsome.

884
01:05:19,528 --> 01:05:21,798
You're flattering me.

885
01:05:21,798 --> 01:05:23,058
Can I give you a hug?

886
01:05:23,058 --> 01:05:25,358
Right now? Here?

887
01:05:27,658 --> 01:05:29,858
I will bring you bad luck.

888
01:05:29,858 --> 01:05:31,858
Don't you think that's stupid?

889
01:05:31,858 --> 01:05:32,858
It seems like...

890
01:05:33,628 --> 01:05:36,158
I killed you.
